    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"/questions/tagged/java\" class=\"post-tag\" title=\"show questions tagged &#39;java&#39;\" rel=\"tag\">java</a> and <a href=\"/questions/tagged/javascript\" class=\"post-tag\" title=\"show questions tagged &#39;javascript&#39;\" rel=\"tag\">javascript</a> are different programming languages with about as much in common as Car and Carpet.</p>\n<p>You have written Java but put it in a file with a file extension that marks it as JavaScript. Your IDE is trying to run it as if it were the latter and throwing errors because it is the former.</p>\n<p>Java typically belongs in <code>.java</code> files.</p>\n"
